        "hizbQuarter": 32,
        "sajda": false
      },
      {
        "number": 510,
        "text": "God does accept repentance, but only of those who are guilty of an evil out of ignorance yet quickly repent, and God turns to them again, for God is all-knowing and all-wise.",
        "surah": {
          "number": 4,
          "name": "سُورَةُ النِّسَاءِ",
          "englishName": "An-Nisaa",
          "englishNameTranslation": "The Women",
          "revelationType": "Medinan",
          "numberOfAyahs": 176
        },
        "numberInSurah": 17,
        "juz": 4,
        "manzil": 1,
        "page": 80,
        "ruku": 64,
        "hizbQuarter": 32,
        "sajda": false
      },
      {
        "number": 511,
        "text": "But (He does not accept) the repentance of those who continue indulging in evil until death draws near and they say: \"We now repent;\" nor of those who die disbelieving. For them We have a grievous retribution in wait.",
        "surah": {
          "number": 4,
          "name": "سُورَةُ النِّسَاءِ",
          "englishName": "An-Nisaa",
          "englishNameTranslation": "The Women",
          "revelationType": "Medinan",
          "numberOfAyahs": 176
        },
        "numberInSurah": 18,
        "juz": 4,
        "manzil": 1,
        "page": 80,
        "ruku": 64,
        "hizbQuarter": 32,
        "sajda": false
      },
      {
        "number": 512,
        "text": "O believers, you are not allowed to take perforce the women (of dead relatives) into your heritage, or tyrannise over them in order to deprive them of what you have given them, unless they are guilty of open adultery. Live with them with tolerance and justice even if you do not care for them. For it may well be you may not like a thing, yet God may have endued it with much goodness.",
